WEBVTT

00:02.168 --> 00:05.088
[adventurous music]

00:05.171 --> 00:12.220
♪ ♪

00:34.117 --> 00:36.035
- FORGOTTEN ME ALREADY,
JASPER?

00:36.119 --> 00:39.497
YOU WOULD DO WELL TO REMEMBER.

00:46.963 --> 00:48.131
[grunts]

00:48.214 --> 00:50.258
- RUFUS.

00:53.386 --> 00:55.889
- TIME TO PUT MY PLAN
INTO ACTION, VICTOR.

00:55.972 --> 00:57.265
- HMM?

01:03.229 --> 01:05.230
WHERE DID YOU GET THAT?

01:05.315 --> 01:08.860
- TRUDY'S MEMORY DOCTOR.

01:08.943 --> 01:12.155
- THIS IS
AN EGYPTIAN MEMORY BOX.

01:12.238 --> 01:14.115
THEY BELIEVED YOU COULD
CAPTURE MEMORIES INSIDE.

01:14.199 --> 01:16.951
AND TRUDY'S THERAPIST
GAVE YOU THIS?

01:17.035 --> 01:18.787
- YES, HE USES IT IN HIS WORK.

01:18.870 --> 01:21.623
HE'S DONE AN INCREDIBLE JOB
ON TRUDY.

01:21.706 --> 01:26.461
AND I'VE JUST HAD A DETAILED
DEMONSTRATION OF HOW IT WORKS.

01:26.544 --> 01:29.047
- YOU ARE NOT INTENDING
TO USE IT ON THE STUDENTS.

01:29.130 --> 01:32.383
- ONCE WE HAVE THEM
UNDER OUR CONTROL,

01:32.467 --> 01:34.469
WE CAN USE THEM
TO PLAY THE GAME FOR US.

01:34.552 --> 01:39.015
WE'LL TAKE THE MASK,
AND THEN WHEN I RELEASE THEM

01:39.098 --> 01:40.183
WITH THESE WORDS
FROM THEIR DREAM STATE--

01:40.266 --> 01:45.188
- THEY WON'T REMEMBER
A THING ABOUT IT.

01:45.271 --> 01:47.774
INTERESTING.

01:51.069 --> 01:53.363
- I THOUGHT I'D PAY YOU A VISIT,
JASPER.

01:53.446 --> 01:55.740
IT'S BEEN SO LONG
SINCE I HEARD FROM YOU.

01:55.824 --> 01:57.283
- I WANT NOTHING MORE
TO DO WITH YOU.

01:57.367 --> 02:00.245
- YES, BUT THERE'S
NO GOING BACK

02:00.328 --> 02:01.538
NOW THAT WE'RE ACQUITTED.

02:01.621 --> 02:03.373
- I'LL KEEP YOUR SECRET,
I PROMISE.

02:03.456 --> 02:07.710
- YES, OF COURSE YOU WILL.

02:07.794 --> 02:12.715
BECAUSE YOU KNOW THAT SOMETHING
VERY, VERY BAD

02:12.799 --> 02:17.554
WILL HAPPEN TO YOU AND YOUR
PRECIOUS GODSON IF YOU DON'T.

02:17.637 --> 02:18.721
- FABIAN.

02:18.805 --> 02:20.557
- LUCKILY FOR YOU,

02:20.640 --> 02:24.352
I DON'T NEED YOUR SERVICES
MUCH LONGER.

02:24.435 --> 02:25.603
MY OTHER ASSOCIATE

02:25.687 --> 02:30.024
WILL BE GETTING THE REAL MASK
EVEN AS WE SPEAK.

02:30.108 --> 02:32.944
- BUT WHO IS SHE GETTING IT FOR?

02:33.027 --> 02:35.697
- VERA SEEMS VERY CLOSE
TO VICTOR THESE DAYS.

02:35.780 --> 02:39.742
- WELL, PERHAPS I SHOULD
PAY VERA A VISIT,

02:39.826 --> 02:41.327
FIND OUT WHERE
HER TRUE LOYALTIES LIE.

02:45.415 --> 02:47.834
I'M SO GLAD
WE HAD THIS LITTLE CHAT.

02:47.917 --> 02:50.920
[suspenseful music]

02:51.004 --> 02:55.925
♪ ♪

02:56.009 --> 02:57.051
- JOY!

02:57.135 --> 02:59.512
I CAN EXPLAIN.

02:59.596 --> 03:01.389
[sighs]

03:03.516 --> 03:05.184
- LOOK, LET'S GET THIS
INTO PERSPECTIVE.

03:05.268 --> 03:08.271
TRUDY ONLY FELL
FOR THE MAGIC BOX STUFF

03:08.354 --> 03:08.813
BECAUSE SHE WANTED TO BELIEVE.

03:08.897 --> 03:11.357
WE DON'T.

03:11.441 --> 03:13.026
- OH, DON'T DO THAT.

03:13.109 --> 03:14.611
- TRUDY'S MEMORY DOCTOR,

03:14.694 --> 03:15.778
HE'S NOT A DOCTOR AT ALL.

03:15.862 --> 03:17.614
I JUST SAW HIM
TALKING TO JASPER.

03:17.697 --> 03:19.949
AND THEN
HE TOOK HIS DISGUISE OFF.

03:20.033 --> 03:22.452
AND IT'S RUFUS.
- WHAT?

03:22.535 --> 03:24.454
- AND GET THIS.
VERA'S WORKING FOR HIM.

03:24.537 --> 03:26.247
- IF RUFUS IS A MEMORY DOCTOR,

03:26.331 --> 03:29.375
DOES THIS MEAN THIS BOX THINGY
WILL WORK ON US TOO?

03:29.459 --> 03:31.169
- NO.
IT'S STILL GARBAGE.

03:31.252 --> 03:34.672
BUT ANYWAY,
NOW WE KNOW THEIR PLAN,

03:34.756 --> 03:35.965
WE CAN JUST TELL VERA
TO GET LOST.

03:36.049 --> 03:39.552
- UNLESS WE PRETEND
TO BE UNDER THEIR INFLUENCE.

03:42.180 --> 03:43.514
- TUMBLEWEED MOMENT, FABIAN.

03:43.598 --> 03:44.682
EXPLAIN.

03:44.766 --> 03:46.017
- THINK OF IT THIS WAY.

03:46.100 --> 03:48.353
VICTOR IS PERHAPS
THE BEST SENET PLAYER ALIVE.

03:48.436 --> 03:50.229
HE PROBABLY LEARNED IT
FROM ROBERT AS A BOY,

03:50.313 --> 03:52.231
SO HE WOULD KNOW
ALL OF ROBERT'S STRATEGIES.

03:52.315 --> 03:53.650
- HANG ON.

03:53.733 --> 03:55.318
SO WE LET VICTOR AND VERA THINK

03:55.401 --> 03:57.320
THEY'RE USING US
TO GET THE MASK, BUT REALLY--

03:57.403 --> 03:59.781
- WE WOULD BE USING THEM.

03:59.864 --> 04:00.865
- IT'S CRAZY.

04:00.949 --> 04:01.950
LOOK, I CAN GET YOU
ACROSS THE BOARD.

04:02.033 --> 04:05.161
I JUST NEED MORE TIME.

04:05.244 --> 04:08.748
- WE'RE RUNNING OUT
OF TIME, JOY.

04:08.831 --> 04:11.250
- WELL, I'M IN.

04:11.334 --> 04:12.627
- ME TOO.

04:12.710 --> 04:15.713
AMBER?

04:15.797 --> 04:17.923
- I THINK YOU'RE ALL INSANE.

04:18.007 --> 04:20.551
- AND THAT IS WHY
YOU'LL NEVER BE A SIBUNA.

04:25.765 --> 04:29.602
[chuckling]

04:29.686 --> 04:31.521
- SAY IT.

04:31.604 --> 04:32.730
- MM.
- [giggles]

04:32.814 --> 04:34.816
- [muffled speech]
CHUBBY BUNNIES...[muffled]

04:34.899 --> 04:35.817
- NOPE, ONE MORE.

04:35.900 --> 04:37.777
- [muffled speech]

04:37.860 --> 04:39.028
- COME ON, ONE MORE.
- MM.

04:39.112 --> 04:41.990
- LOOK.
HMM?

04:42.073 --> 04:43.408
AH.

04:43.491 --> 04:46.202
[muffled speech]
CHUBBY BUNNIES...[muffled]

04:46.286 --> 04:49.372
HM-MM.
ONE MORE.

04:49.455 --> 04:51.749
[muffled speech]
CHUBBY BUNNIES...[muffled]

04:51.833 --> 04:53.209
- OH, THEY'RE--
THEY'RE COMING OUT.

04:53.293 --> 04:55.837
THAT'S GROSS.
- [giggles]

04:55.920 --> 04:58.756
- UGH.
[phone ringing]

05:03.011 --> 05:04.429
OH, IT'S MICK.

05:04.512 --> 05:06.723
- RIGHT.
[ringing continues]

05:06.806 --> 05:08.349
YOU WANT ME TO...

05:08.433 --> 05:10.101
- DO YOU MIND?

05:10.184 --> 05:12.228
- NO, WHY WOULD I MIND?

05:12.311 --> 05:15.606
BUT I'M KEEPING THESE.
[grunts]

05:15.690 --> 05:17.734
- JEROME.

05:17.817 --> 05:19.777
SORRY.

05:19.861 --> 05:24.615
- IT'S ALL RIGHT.
I KNOW MY PLACE.

05:24.699 --> 05:27.410
- [sighs]

05:27.493 --> 05:29.996
MICK, HI.

05:32.081 --> 05:33.666
- DR. ALEXANDER SAID

05:33.750 --> 05:35.960
THAT IF YOU SHARE THE MEMORY BOX
WITH A FRIEND,

05:36.044 --> 05:38.963
THEN SWEET DREAMS WILL COME

05:39.047 --> 05:43.009
TO BOTH THE GIVER
AND THE RECEIVER.

05:43.092 --> 05:45.053
ISN'T THAT
SUCH A LOVELY THOUGHT?

05:45.136 --> 05:46.554
- AW, HOW LOVELY.
- LOVELY.

05:46.637 --> 05:47.764
- VERY SWEET.

05:47.847 --> 05:49.807
- AND HE GAVE ME
THIS REALLY CLEVER EXERCISE

05:49.891 --> 05:50.892
TO HELP ME TO SLEEP.

05:50.975 --> 05:52.769
SHALL I SHOW YOU?

05:52.852 --> 05:54.937
OH, WHERE'S THE BOX?

05:55.021 --> 05:57.774
OH, I THINK VERA HAD IT LAST.

05:57.857 --> 05:58.941
- OKAY, READY?

05:59.025 --> 06:02.278
OKAY, JUST STAY FOCUSED,
AND WE'LL BE OKAY.

06:02.361 --> 06:03.321
JUST KEEP TELLING YOURSELF,
"IT'S ALL GARBAGE."

06:03.404 --> 06:05.323
- IT'S GARBAGE.
IT'S GARBAGE.

06:05.406 --> 06:06.866
IT'S GARBAGE.
- [clears throat]

06:06.949 --> 06:09.452
IN YOUR HEAD, ALFIE.

06:09.535 --> 06:10.536
- WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

06:10.620 --> 06:11.579
- WHAT?

06:11.662 --> 06:14.082
- I SAID, "WHAT ARE YOU DOING?"

06:14.165 --> 06:16.793
- IN CASE SHE STARTS CHANTING.

06:16.876 --> 06:18.628
I DON'T TAKE ANY RISKS.

06:18.711 --> 06:19.921
- AMBER, DON'T...

06:25.009 --> 06:27.970
- NOW...

06:28.054 --> 06:30.139
AS SOON AS I OPEN THE LID,

06:30.223 --> 06:34.685
LOOK INSIDE,
AND ALL YOUR THOUGHTS...

06:34.769 --> 06:36.020
- HAVE YOU SEEN THE TIME, TRUDY?

06:36.104 --> 06:38.815
DIDN'T DR. ALEXANDER
RECOMMEND AN EARLY NIGHT?

06:38.898 --> 06:40.483
- OH, YES.

06:40.566 --> 06:42.693
I DO FEEL A BIT DRAINED.

06:42.777 --> 06:43.986
I WAS JUST ABOUT TO SHOW THEM--

06:44.070 --> 06:45.238
- OH, I CAN TAKE IT FROM HERE.

06:45.321 --> 06:46.155
YOU CERTAINLY TALKED ME
THROUGH IT ENOUGH.

06:46.239 --> 06:48.199
- OH, THANKS, VERA.

06:48.282 --> 06:49.033
I WILL TURN IN, I THINK.

06:49.117 --> 06:50.326
GOOD NIGHT, EVERYONE.

06:50.409 --> 06:54.747
SWEET DREAMS.
[laughs lightly]

06:59.377 --> 07:01.879
- RIGHT.

07:01.963 --> 07:04.507
LIKE TRUDY SAID,

07:04.590 --> 07:07.426
LOOK INTO THE BOX.

07:07.510 --> 07:10.471
[eerie music]

07:10.555 --> 07:15.560
♪ ♪

07:23.943 --> 07:28.322
- VERA, IS THAT YOU?

07:28.406 --> 07:32.243
- THAT'S IT, THROUGH HERE,
ALL OF YOU.

07:35.788 --> 07:36.247
- IT WORKED?

07:36.330 --> 07:38.040
- LIKE A DREAM.

07:38.124 --> 07:39.250
IN FACT,
AS FAR AS THEY'RE CONCERNED,

07:39.333 --> 07:41.002
THAT'S WHAT THIS IS,
A DREAM.

07:41.085 --> 07:43.045
THEY'LL TAKE ORDERS,
BUT THEY CAN'T TALK BACK.

07:43.129 --> 07:44.380
THE PERFECT TEENAGERS.

07:44.463 --> 07:48.050
- EXCELLENT.

07:48.134 --> 07:50.803
EXCELLENT.

07:53.848 --> 07:57.059
UM, ALFIE LEWIS,

07:57.143 --> 08:01.355
WOULD YOU LIKE A SLICE
OF CHOCOLATE CAKE BEFORE WE GO?

08:07.528 --> 08:09.238
JUST TESTING.

08:09.322 --> 08:10.364
- TRUST ME, VICTOR,

08:10.448 --> 08:12.950
THE MEMORY BOX
WORKED LIKE A CHARM.

08:13.034 --> 08:14.410
IT'S OVER TO YOU NOW.

08:14.493 --> 08:15.453
DO YOU KNOW WHAT TO DO?

08:15.536 --> 08:18.122
- WELL, WITH ROBERT
AS AN OPPONENT,

08:18.206 --> 08:20.625
ONE CAN NEVER BE
ABSOLUTELY SURE,

08:20.708 --> 08:22.251
BUT I THINK SO.

08:22.335 --> 08:25.379
[creaking]

08:27.173 --> 08:28.132
- JUST THINK, VICTOR.

08:28.216 --> 08:30.092
SOON, THE MASK
WILL REALLY BE OURS.

08:30.176 --> 08:32.094
- INDEED.

08:32.178 --> 08:34.597
FOLLOW VERA.

08:34.679 --> 08:36.599
GO ON.

08:36.682 --> 08:38.683
GO ON, THAT'S IT.

08:38.768 --> 08:40.770
THAT'S IT.

08:40.852 --> 08:42.605
GO ON.

08:47.235 --> 08:50.279
[creaking]

08:53.032 --> 08:55.117
- SO DAD'S FLYING BACK
ON BUSINESS LATER THIS EVENING.

08:55.201 --> 08:58.579
I WISH I COULD COME WITH HIM,
BUT I'VE A BIG CUP GAME AND...

09:02.041 --> 09:03.000
MARA?

09:03.084 --> 09:05.711
- SORRY?

09:05.795 --> 09:07.838
- YOU ZONED OUT.

09:07.922 --> 09:11.008
IS EVERYTHING OKAY?

09:11.092 --> 09:13.219
- YOU KNOW WHEN YOU ASKED ME

09:13.302 --> 09:17.765
IF I THOUGHT THIS WHOLE
LONG-DISTANCE THING WAS WORKING?

09:17.848 --> 09:20.142
- THERE'S SOMEONE ELSE,
ISN'T THERE?

09:20.226 --> 09:22.562
- MICK, THAT'S NOT
WHAT THIS IS ABOUT.

09:29.068 --> 09:33.322
"SORRY, JEROME.

09:33.406 --> 09:37.451
CAN WE TALK?"

09:43.207 --> 09:44.875
- VERA?

09:58.681 --> 09:59.932
HELLO, JEROME.

10:00.016 --> 10:01.767
YOU SEE, I CAN'T RISK YOU
RAISING THE ALARM,

10:01.851 --> 10:03.436
SO THERE ARE TWO WAYS
THAT WE ARE GONNA DO THIS:

10:03.519 --> 10:05.938
THE EASY WAY OR THE HARD WAY.

10:06.022 --> 10:08.357
BUT EITHER WAY, YOU ARE
COMING WITH ME, UNDERSTOOD?

10:08.441 --> 10:13.029
- NO, NO, NO.

10:13.112 --> 10:14.655
- HEY, JER--

10:14.739 --> 10:18.701
UH, HI.

10:18.784 --> 10:20.870
IS EVERYTHING OKAY HERE?

10:20.953 --> 10:22.955
[suspenseful music]

10:23.039 --> 10:28.127
♪ ♪

10:28.210 --> 10:33.424
- RUTTER, MISS WILLIAMSON,
AND MISS MILLINGTON,

10:33.507 --> 10:36.177
TAKE ONE STEP FORWARDS.

10:36.260 --> 10:39.221
[tense music]

10:39.305 --> 10:42.683
♪ ♪

10:42.767 --> 10:45.561
LEWIS.

10:45.644 --> 10:47.855
LEWIS.

10:47.938 --> 10:51.567
LEWIS.
SO VERY CLEVER, ROBERT.

10:51.650 --> 10:54.403
THIS SENET BOARD
HAS ENEMY PIECES

10:54.487 --> 10:55.905
WHICH ARE MUCH HARDER TO BEAT.

10:55.988 --> 10:57.907
- IT'S THE SAME AS
THE MINIATURE VERSION, ISN'T IT?

10:57.990 --> 10:59.992
IF YOU LAND ON A JACKAL SQUARE,
THEY COULD TAKE YOU.

11:00.076 --> 11:03.579
- YES, BUT THEY ALL SPIN
ACCORDING TO A SET PATTERN.

11:03.662 --> 11:05.915
THIS ONE HERE
ALWAYS TURNS TWO SQUARES

11:05.998 --> 11:07.416
IN A CLOCKWISE DIRECTION.

11:07.500 --> 11:09.877
BUT I NEED MORE TIME
TO PREDICT THE OTHERS.

11:09.960 --> 11:11.045
- JUST DO IT.

11:11.128 --> 11:12.088
- HE DOESN'T KNOW
WHAT HE'S DOING.

11:12.171 --> 11:13.339
- [whispers]
ALFIE, SHH.

11:15.341 --> 11:19.470
- LEWIS...

11:19.553 --> 11:23.682
STEP...

11:23.766 --> 11:25.017
LEFT.

11:25.101 --> 11:27.228
- FABIAN.
- ALFIE.

11:27.311 --> 11:31.482
- LEWIS, TAKE ONE STEP LEFT.

11:31.565 --> 11:33.818
- FABIAN, I CAN'T.
- ALFIE, DO IT.

11:33.901 --> 11:36.445
- WHAT IS GOING ON?
WHY ISN'T HE DOING IT?

11:36.529 --> 11:37.363
- DO IT.

11:37.446 --> 11:40.449
[suspenseful music]

11:40.533 --> 11:45.538
♪ ♪

11:48.999 --> 11:50.251
- HE DOESN'T KNOW
WHAT HE'S DOING.

11:50.334 --> 11:53.629
- LEWIS, TAKE ONE STEP LEFT.

11:53.712 --> 11:56.173
- FABIAN, I CAN'T.
- ALFIE, DO IT.

11:56.257 --> 11:58.717
- WHAT IS GOING ON?
WHY ISN'T HE DOING IT?

11:58.801 --> 12:01.887
[suspenseful music]

12:01.971 --> 12:08.269
♪ ♪

12:08.352 --> 12:09.311
- [screams]

12:09.395 --> 12:12.273
- [gasps]

12:12.356 --> 12:13.232
- WHAT WAS THAT?

12:13.315 --> 12:14.650
I TELL YOU,
I HEARD SOMETHING.

12:14.733 --> 12:20.156
- YES, THE SOUND OF A BOY
FALLING TO AN UNCERTAIN FATE.

12:20.239 --> 12:22.867
HARMING THE STUDENTS
WAS NEVER PART OF THE PLAN.

12:22.950 --> 12:24.326
- WELL, YOU CAN'T
MAKE AN OMELET

12:24.410 --> 12:26.287
WITHOUT BREAKING A FEW...

12:26.370 --> 12:30.332
- RELEASE THEM.

12:30.416 --> 12:31.876
- NO.

12:31.959 --> 12:36.297
- RUTTER, WILLIAMSON,
MILLINGTON, TURN AROUND.

12:39.550 --> 12:42.052
SAY THE RELEASE WORDS.

12:42.136 --> 12:44.555
- VICTOR, THE--
- SAY THEM!

12:44.638 --> 12:46.682
- [sighs]

12:50.269 --> 12:53.105
[speaking foreign language]

12:55.983 --> 12:58.944
[tense music]

12:59.028 --> 13:04.575
♪ ♪

13:04.658 --> 13:06.410
- ALFIE!

13:06.494 --> 13:07.703
WE LOST HIM.

13:07.786 --> 13:10.039
- VICTOR'S A BRILLIANT
SENET PLAYER, IS HE?

13:10.122 --> 13:11.123
- ALL RIGHT, I GOT IT WRONG.

13:11.207 --> 13:12.082
- BIG TIME.

13:12.166 --> 13:13.542
FOR A MINUTE BACK THERE,

13:13.626 --> 13:14.376
I THOUGHT THEY'D ACTUALLY
TAKEN CONTROL OF YOU.

13:14.460 --> 13:16.295
- GUYS.
ALFIE.

13:16.378 --> 13:18.547
COME ON, FABIAN.

13:18.631 --> 13:21.634
WE HAVE TO FIND OUT
IF HE'S WITH NINA.

13:21.717 --> 13:25.638
- COME BACK THE WAY YOU CAME.

13:25.721 --> 13:27.431
- HOW RUDE,
I'M, UH--I'M RENE ZELDMAN.

13:27.515 --> 13:29.725
I'M JEROME'S UNCLE.

13:29.808 --> 13:32.311
- OH, PLEASURE TO MEET YOU,
UNCLE RENE.

13:32.394 --> 13:34.313
- JEROME'S A LITTLE UPSET.

13:34.396 --> 13:36.565
A FAVORITE AUNT OF HIS
HAS JUST PASSED AWAY.

13:36.649 --> 13:37.858
- OH.

13:37.942 --> 13:38.901
- WE'RE JUST LEAVING.

13:38.984 --> 13:39.902
- NO, WE WEREN'T.

13:39.985 --> 13:41.654
- YES, WE ARE.

13:41.737 --> 13:44.406
OR PERHAPS I SHOULD
GO GET POPPY TOO?

13:44.490 --> 13:45.866
WHAT DO YOU THINK ABOUT THAT,
JEROME?

13:45.950 --> 13:47.034
- N-NO, NOT POPPY.

13:47.117 --> 13:49.537
- NO, NO, YOU'RE RIGHT.

13:49.620 --> 13:53.165
SHE'S TOO YOUNG
TO COPE WITH BEREAVEMENT.

13:53.249 --> 13:54.792
WE'LL GO BY OURSELVES.

13:54.875 --> 13:57.753
COME ALONG.
COME ALONG.

13:57.836 --> 14:01.257
UNCLE PETER
IS DESPERATE TO SEE YOU.

14:04.343 --> 14:05.594
- HUH.

14:05.678 --> 14:09.557
BRITS.
[can hissing]

14:17.106 --> 14:18.941
- IF WE GET CAUGHT
BREAKING INTO THE SCHOOL,

14:19.024 --> 14:20.359
WE'RE GONNA BE IN BIG TROUBLE.

14:20.442 --> 14:21.235
- THAT'S THE LEAST
OF OUR WORRIES, JOY.

14:21.318 --> 14:23.112
[both gasp]

14:23.195 --> 14:24.572
UGH.

14:24.655 --> 14:26.282
- I BROUGHT THEM SUPPLIES
FROM THE MACHINE.

14:26.365 --> 14:29.451
IF YOU DON'T FEED ALFIE
EVERY HALF AN HOUR, HE TURNS.

14:29.535 --> 14:32.413
- AND WE'RE IN.

14:32.496 --> 14:34.873
OKAY, ALL RIGHT.

14:38.210 --> 14:40.462
NINA?
NINA, CAN YOU HEAR ME?

14:40.546 --> 14:42.506
- YES, YES, I CAN HEAR YOU.

14:42.590 --> 14:44.174
- UM, IS ALFIE WITH YOU?

14:44.258 --> 14:46.510
- YEAH, HE'S HERE.

14:46.594 --> 14:48.554
A LITTLE SHAKEN UP,
BUT HE'S GOOD.

14:48.637 --> 14:51.724
- NINA, I'M SENDING DOWN
HIS FAVORITE SNACKS.

14:51.807 --> 14:54.143
LOOK AFTER HIM FOR ME,
WON'T YOU?

14:54.226 --> 14:56.395
- COURSE I WILL.

15:01.817 --> 15:03.861
GOT IT.
THANKS.

15:03.944 --> 15:06.488
- UM, TELL ALFIE I'M SORRY.

15:06.572 --> 15:08.115
IT WAS--IT WAS A STUPID IDEA.

15:08.198 --> 15:10.034
- HEY, IT COULD HAVE WORKED.

15:10.117 --> 15:11.827
WE HAD TO TRY.

15:11.910 --> 15:15.080
- YEAH, DON'T BEAT YOURSELF UP
OVER IT.

15:15.164 --> 15:16.665
- LOOK, UM,

15:16.749 --> 15:18.334
WE'RE GONNA GET YOU BOTH OUT OF
THERE REALLY SOON, ALL RIGHT?

15:18.417 --> 15:21.837
I PROMISE.

15:21.920 --> 15:24.173
AREN'T WE?

15:24.256 --> 15:27.009
YEAH.

15:27.092 --> 15:29.928
- [sighs]

15:30.012 --> 15:32.097
[cell phone ringing]

15:38.520 --> 15:39.480
- RUFUS.

15:39.563 --> 15:42.024
- I CAME TO SEE YOU TONIGHT,
VERA.

15:42.107 --> 15:45.235
TELL ME YOU WERE OUT SECURING
THE MASK OF ANUBIS FOR ME.

15:45.319 --> 15:46.362
- ALMOST.

15:46.445 --> 15:47.863
THE PLAN WENT A LITTLE AWRY,

15:47.946 --> 15:49.698
BUT DON'T WORRY;
THERE'S A BACKUP PLAN.

15:49.782 --> 15:53.202
- WELL, YOU BETTER NOT BE LYING,
FOR YOUR SAKE, VERA.

15:53.285 --> 15:54.912
OH, AND BY THE WAY,
IF ANYONE ASKS,

15:54.995 --> 15:58.040
JEROME CLARKE
IS VISITING HIS UNCLE.

15:58.123 --> 15:59.333
- JEROME?

15:59.416 --> 16:01.377
- OH, DON'T WORRY.
HE'S PERFECTLY SAFE.

16:04.838 --> 16:07.174
FOR NOW.

16:15.224 --> 16:18.352
- SO I KNOW
WE'RE NOT COMPATIBLE,

16:18.435 --> 16:20.979
BUT I STILL REALLY LIKE YOU.

16:21.063 --> 16:22.439
NO.

16:22.523 --> 16:25.651
JEROME, WE'VE HAD
OUR UPS AND DOWNS.

16:25.734 --> 16:27.361
NO.

16:27.444 --> 16:31.657
JEROME, REMEMBER WHEN
I TURNED YOU DOWN THAT TIME?

16:31.740 --> 16:34.201
MM-MM.

16:34.284 --> 16:36.245
[whispers]
OKAY.

16:39.581 --> 16:45.379
[knock at door]

16:45.462 --> 16:48.006
JEROME?

16:48.090 --> 16:49.967
ALFIE?

16:53.721 --> 16:55.597
- AMBER, WHAT ARE YOU...

16:55.681 --> 16:58.016
- I GET LOW BLOOD SUGAR.

16:58.100 --> 17:00.436
AND IT'S RUDE TO STARE.

17:00.519 --> 17:01.353
- ANYONE SEEN JEROME
THIS MORNING?

17:01.437 --> 17:03.313
OR ALFIE?

17:03.397 --> 17:04.606
- UH, ALFIE'S SICK.

17:04.690 --> 17:08.026
- YEAH, UM, HE'S GOT...

17:08.109 --> 17:11.155
COCO POCKS.

17:11.238 --> 17:14.450
- UM, YEAH, HE'S GONE OVER
TO SEE THE NURSE.

17:14.532 --> 17:16.617
BETTER TO GET SOMETHING
LIKE THAT CHECKED OUT, REALLY.

17:16.702 --> 17:17.578
- YEAH.

17:17.661 --> 17:18.328
- AND JEROME?

17:18.412 --> 17:19.829
- NO IDEA WHERE JEROME IS.

17:19.913 --> 17:21.874
- OH, I-I SAW HIM LAST NIGHT.

17:21.957 --> 17:22.583
HE LEFT WITH HIS UNCLE.

17:22.665 --> 17:25.252
- OH, WHAT UNCLE?

17:25.335 --> 17:28.338
- I DON'T KNOW.
BIZARRE.

17:37.306 --> 17:42.936
- VICTOR, WE NEED TO TALK
ABOUT LAST NIGHT.

17:43.020 --> 17:44.146
WHO WERE YOU CALLING?

17:44.229 --> 17:45.981
- I WAS CONSIDERING CONTACTING
MR. SWEET.

17:46.064 --> 17:48.650
- WHAT FOR?
- ALFIE LEWIS!

17:48.734 --> 17:50.444
- CALM YOURSELF, VICTOR.

17:50.527 --> 17:52.154
THERE IS NOTHING TO SUGGEST THAT
THE BOY HAS COME TO ANY HARM.

17:52.237 --> 17:54.865
- HE HAS DISAPPEARED,
HAS HE NOT?

17:54.948 --> 17:57.367
- YES, BUT HIS FRIENDS
DON'T SEEM TO BE PANICKING

17:57.451 --> 18:01.872
OR ASKING QUESTIONS
ABOUT WHERE HE'S GONE, DO THEY?

18:01.955 --> 18:04.041
- WHAT ARE YOU SAYING, VERA?

18:04.124 --> 18:05.292
- I AM WONDERING WHY.

18:05.375 --> 18:07.503
UNLESS, OF COURSE,
THEY KNOW WHERE HE IS

18:07.586 --> 18:08.670
AND THAT HE'S SAFE.

18:08.754 --> 18:13.926
SO PERHAPS...

18:14.009 --> 18:14.927
- PERHAPS?

18:15.010 --> 18:16.220
- YOU WERE RIGHT

18:16.303 --> 18:19.181
AND THEY WERE PRETENDING
TO BE UNDER OUR CONTROL.

18:19.264 --> 18:24.978
IN WHICH CASE,
WE NEED TO FIND A PLAN "B."

18:25.062 --> 18:26.313
LEAVE IT TO VERA.

18:38.283 --> 18:41.995
- AND THEN YOU BOUGHT ME
A CACTUS AS A PRESENT.

18:42.079 --> 18:43.247
- WHAT WAS I THINKING?

18:43.330 --> 18:45.457
- NO ONE'S EVER
BOUGHT ME A CACTUS BEFORE.

18:45.541 --> 18:50.254
AND THERE IS A GOOD REASON
FOR THAT, BUT IT WAS SWEET.

18:50.337 --> 18:55.342
YOU KNOW, YOU BEING DOWN THERE
HAS MADE ME REALIZE,

18:55.425 --> 18:59.721
I THINK WE SHOULD GIVE
AMFIE ANOTHER GO.

18:59.805 --> 19:01.682
- OH, NO, I'M STAYING OUT OF IT.

19:01.765 --> 19:02.516
- ALFIE?

19:02.599 --> 19:04.560
DID YOU HEAR WHAT I JUST SAID?

19:04.643 --> 19:07.813
- UH, CAN I...

19:07.896 --> 19:10.691
CAN I THINK ABOUT IT?

19:10.774 --> 19:13.944
- THINK ABOUT IT?
THINK ABOUT WHAT?

19:14.027 --> 19:16.405
WHAT IS THERE TO THINK ABOUT?

19:17.823 --> 19:21.368
- HEY, MARA, DAD'S GOT
A DATE FOR HIS PAROLE HEARING.

19:21.451 --> 19:23.412
- THAT'S AMAZING.

19:23.495 --> 19:25.998
- HAVE YOU SEEN JEROME ANYWHERE?

19:26.081 --> 19:27.583
- HE'S AT YOUR UNCLE'S,
ISN'T HE?

19:27.666 --> 19:28.750
- IS HE?

19:28.834 --> 19:29.751
- THAT'S WHAT I HEARD.

19:29.835 --> 19:31.712
HE PICKED HIM UP YESTERDAY.

19:31.795 --> 19:35.257
- THAT'S WEIRD.
UNCLE DAVID OR UNCLE SIMON?

19:35.340 --> 19:36.675
REALLY WEIRD.

19:36.758 --> 19:40.596
I'LL GIVE HIM A CALL.

19:40.679 --> 19:43.557
- SO BY SUNSET TOMORROW,
OUR TIME IS UP.

19:43.640 --> 19:44.975
ARE WE ALL FOR
GOING DOWN THIS EVENING

19:45.058 --> 19:47.227
AND FINISHING THIS THING?

19:47.311 --> 19:47.603
- JOY?

19:47.686 --> 19:49.938
- RIGHT.

19:50.022 --> 19:52.566
- WELL, FILMING EVERYTHING
ON THIS HAS REALLY HELPED.

19:52.649 --> 19:55.193
THERE'S A DEFINITE PATTERN
TO THE GUARD'S MOVEMENTS.

19:55.277 --> 19:57.571
I'M JUST TRYING
TO PLOT A SAFE PATH ACROSS.

19:57.654 --> 19:59.781
- AND?

19:59.865 --> 20:02.284
- I'LL GET IT.
DON'T WORRY.

20:02.367 --> 20:05.370
BUT TONIGHT'S A LITTLE TOO SOON.

20:05.454 --> 20:08.123
SORRY, AFTER WHAT HAPPENED
LAST TIME, BETTER TO BE SAFE.

20:08.206 --> 20:11.418
- WE'RE CUTTING THIS CLOSE.

20:11.501 --> 20:13.128
- ALL THIS WHISPERING.

20:13.211 --> 20:14.630
GUY COULD DEVELOP A COMPLEX
AROUND HERE.

20:14.713 --> 20:15.464
[chuckles]

20:15.547 --> 20:18.467
- OH, OH, GOSH.
- OH, WE, UM...

20:18.550 --> 20:20.969
YEAH, AMBER,
YOU'VE GOT TO BE THERE?

20:21.053 --> 20:21.970
GOT TO GO.

20:22.054 --> 20:25.015
- SORRY.
- BYE.

20:25.098 --> 20:26.975
- RIGHT.

20:29.603 --> 20:30.812
- WE'RE--WE'RE NOT WHISPERING
ABOUT YOU.

20:30.896 --> 20:32.981
DON'T WORRY.

20:33.065 --> 20:34.232
- WELL, WHAT WERE YOU
WHISPERING ABOUT?

20:34.316 --> 20:37.361
WHERE DID YOU GUYS ALL
DISAPPEAR TO LAST NIGHT?

20:37.444 --> 20:40.822
- IF I TOLD YOU,
I'D HAVE TO WIPE YOUR MEMORY

20:40.906 --> 20:42.908
AND GET YOU DEPORTED.

20:42.991 --> 20:44.326
[both laugh nervously]

20:49.081 --> 20:50.040
- ANOTHER SEEKER OF THE MASK?

20:50.123 --> 20:52.918
- YES.
HE'S ON MY SIDE.

20:55.337 --> 20:58.423
YOU SAID THE MASK
HAD SPECIAL POWERS.

20:58.507 --> 20:59.091
- YEAH.

20:59.174 --> 21:02.552
- WELL, WHAT DOES IT DO?

21:02.636 --> 21:06.181
AND CAN I ASK
WHY YOU WERE SEARCHING FOR?

21:06.264 --> 21:10.185
- I WANTED THE TEARS OF GOLD,
OF COURSE.

21:10.269 --> 21:14.189
I LONGED FOR IMMORTALITY
IN THIS LIFE,

21:14.272 --> 21:16.817
NOT SOME EGYPTIAN AFTERLIFE.

21:16.900 --> 21:17.693
- EGYPTIAN AFTERLIFE?

21:17.776 --> 21:19.987
- YEAH.

21:20.070 --> 21:22.280
WHOEVER WEARS
THE MASK OF ANUBIS--

21:22.364 --> 21:25.242
- YOU HAVE SAID ENOUGH,
OLD MAN.

21:25.325 --> 21:26.702
- I MUST GO.

21:26.785 --> 21:27.744
- NO.

21:27.828 --> 21:29.538
MR. RODENMAAR.

21:29.621 --> 21:33.250
- I AM WEARY OF WAITING,
CHOSEN ONE.

21:33.333 --> 21:35.377
- YOUR FRIENDS DO NOT HAVE LONG.

21:35.460 --> 21:39.381
AND THEN I WILL REPLACE YOU.

21:39.464 --> 21:40.841
- WHAT DO YOU MEAN?

21:45.637 --> 21:47.889
- ARE YOU HE?

21:47.973 --> 21:49.933
- WE NEED MORE TIME.

21:50.017 --> 21:54.062
- TELL ME, BOY.
ARE YOU HE?

21:54.146 --> 21:56.106
THE CHOSEN ONE IS FAILING.

21:56.189 --> 21:58.650
I MUST WAKE THE OSIRIAN.

21:58.734 --> 22:00.527
ARE YOU HE?

22:00.610 --> 22:03.905
- SMOKEY, LEAVE HIM ALONE.

22:03.989 --> 22:05.615
- YOU SEE ME TOO?

22:05.699 --> 22:08.285
PERHAPS THE OSIRIAN
SLEEPS IN YOU.

22:08.368 --> 22:09.244
- WHAT?

22:09.327 --> 22:10.495
- TAKE MY HAND, BOY.

22:14.207 --> 22:16.501
- NO, EDDIE, DON'T.

22:16.585 --> 22:18.086
- A BORN PROTECTOR.

22:18.170 --> 22:22.215
PERHAPS IT IS YOU AFTER ALL.

22:22.299 --> 22:24.968
- I DON'T KNOW WHAT YOU MEAN.

22:25.052 --> 22:27.429
- YOU WILL TELL ME.
